ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Position for eating: adequate head/trunk control
Notes: 0 =  No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: Alerts to food stimulus within two seconds (leaning forward and/or opening mouth; head and/or body orientated towards food
Notes: 0 =  No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: Mandibular Stability: smooth, rhythmic sequence; graded jaw opening. Absence of jaw thrusting and weak chewing.
Notes: 0 =  No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: Lip/Tongue Movement: Isolated excursion of the tongue in one smooth movement
Notes: 0 =  No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: Oral Sensitivity to Food Texture: accepts food. Absence of gagging, choking, and/or food rejection.
Notes: 0 =  No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: Oral Sensitivity to Food Texture: able to create adequate labial seal to facilitate intraoral pressure when drinking from a spoon, cup, or bottle-lips close around cup or spood. Food/liquid enters mouth and absesnse of incomplete lip seal.
Notes: 0 =  No; 1 = Yes
